org.hibernate.metamodel.model.domain.spi

Interface Lockable<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AllowableParameterType<T>, Bindable<T>, DomainType<T>, DomainTypeDescriptor<T>, EmbeddedContainer<T>, EntityDomainType<T>, EntityType<T>, EntityTypeDescriptor<T>, EntityValuedExpressableType<T>, EntityValuedNavigable<T>, ExpressableType<T>, Filterable, IdentifiableDomainType<T>, IdentifiableType<T>, IdentifiableTypeDescriptor<T>, InheritanceCapable<T>, ManagedDomainType<T>, ManagedType<T>, ManagedTypeDescriptor<T>, Navigable<T>, NavigableContainer<T>, RootTableGroupProducer, Serializable, SimpleDomainType<T>, SimpleTypeDescriptor<T>, StateArrayContributorContainer, TableGroupProducer, TableReferenceContributor, Type<T>, Writeable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractEntityTypeDescriptor

    public interface Lockable<T>
extends EntityTypeDescriptor<T>
    Contract for things that can be locked via a LockingStrategy.

    Currently only the root table gets locked, except for the case of HQL and Criteria queries against dialects which do not support either (1) FOR UPDATE OF or (2) support hint locking (in which case *all* queried tables would be locked).

    Since:
    3.2
